By default, when ag-Grid performs an aggregation, it will ignore any null values and calculate the aggregation based on the non-null values. So if you have null values displayed as "N/A" in your grid, the aggregation will simply treat them as if they are null and exclude them from the calculation.

However, you can also configure the aggregation to include null values in the calculation by setting the `aggFunc` property in the column definition to a custom aggregation function that handles null values as you see fit. For example, you could use the following custom aggregation function to treat "N/A" as a null value and include it in the calculation:
```javascript
{
